Corrosion Engineer
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/04/30 09:01:10
Ref. JB3045756
Job Description
UAE / Iraq - Design & Engineering Team
Duties and Responsibilities:
Develop, implement, and continuously improve the Corrosion Management Programs, this includes mitigation activities such as: Materials Section, Cathodic Protection, Coatings, Chemical Inhibition and monitoring activities such as: Corrosion Probes, Fluid Sample Analysis, Equipment Inspection. Also provide support to the Pipeline Engineering team in implementation the pipeline corrosion control programs.
Skills
 Minimum 7 years in corrosion engineering and surveillance in the hydrocarbon processing industry with a good knowledge of metallurgy. Experience with gas dehydration and acid gas
absorption systems.
 Experience in an operating environment is necessary.
 Understanding of safety and environmental requirements and risk assessment.
 Must have a high level of computer literacy with a strong knowledge of Microsoft Office software and integrated business systems (. SAP).
 Good adaptability to a multinational environment. Good interpersonal skills and the ability to work with and supervise a team.
 Strong communication, leadership, and judgment skills.
Qualifications
- Bachelors Degree in Metallurgical (Preferred)
- Professional Qualification is an advantage.
