About This Company
China Petroleum Engineering & Construction Corporation (CPECC), with more than 50 years’ history and starting overseas business in 1980, is a large-scale enterprise specialized in contracting international petroleum and petrochemical projects, and has been the largest and leading contractor in the field of international oil/gas engineering and construction in China.
We consistently abide by the operation philosophy of “Credibility, Innovation, Quality and Efficiency”. Over the years, We have constituted five regional markets that have taken shapes in North Africa, Central Asia, South Asia, South America and Middle East, and have completed quite a large number of oil/gas production bases, large and medium-sized refineries, petrochemical plants, chemical fertilizer plants, long-distance oil/gas transmission pipeline, large-scale oil/gas storage terminals and Tank farms, roads, bridges, and other municipal utilities successfully.
CPECC (Iraq), which is the branch of CPECC, is in charge of the contracts in Iraq. Since 2009, we have completed a variety of oil and gas projects in Ahdeb Oil Filed, Halfaya oil field and Rumila oil field in Iraq. So far several projects are still in executing and we are preparing some new projects simultaneously in the Southern Iraq.
CPECC (Iraq) provide dynamic and static security measures for all projects in Iraq. There are trebling security assigned for camp and job site. Security information and alert are provided by the Tribals, Local Authrities and International Agencies on the first level. Physical security protections like steel fence, ditch, soil beam, guarded towers and T-wall etc.on the second level.
When in transport, armed vehicles will be accompanied and guarded by securities. Up to now, we have mobilized thousands of employees to and fro Iraq with no hazard happened. Moreover, there are still hundreds of employees working at different sites in Iraq at present.
